UralSib Bank, a Russian non-state
lender, may appoint Ilkka Salonen as chief executive officer to
help restore profitability and prepare the bank for a public
share sale,  Kommersant  reported, citing unidentified people.  Salonen has been working in  Russia  since 1985 at lenders
including  Nordea Bank AB (NDA)  and OAO Sberbank, the newspaper said.
Until recently, he represented the European Bank of
Reconstruction and Development on the board of Promsvyazbank,
according to Kommersant.  To contact the reporter on this story:
